@ineiti You seem to be thinking of capacity factor, which for solar plants is on the range of 20% to 30% with bifacial panels.

The PV cell efficiency is irrelevant here, or rather, already factored into the overall capacity.

But also keep in mind this is an *annual* production capacity

@Adventure_aaron @wheatfrom @fasc1nate I'll preface this by saying I generally agree it's a vine...

There is no universally agreed upon precise definition of a "tree", either botanically or in common language.

Monocots can even be trees (banana, palm, bamboo)

@wvcaspel Doel 3 is not "a perfect plant".

Its reactor pressure vessel contains tens of thousands of hairline cracks as a result of hydrogen flaking occurring at fabrication time, the first time such a defect has been observed in a nuclear reactor.
